=Description=

"Robohand Australia is not for profit charity who's mission is to make functional hands available to anyone who needs them. We are a team of volunteers who have been developing and manufacturing 3D printed hands since 2013. We share our designs so that anyone with access to a 3D printer can make and maintain a hand of their own. We also manufacture and soon sell hands and components with all profits going towards hands for those who cannot afford them, improving existing hands, and development of new aid devices."
(http://www.robohandaustralia.com/about_us)

